main event: A sighting of unusual objects was reported in Manitowoc, Wisconsin on September 8, 1962, involving saucer-shaped, silver objects that appeared to be rotating and flying at an estimated altitude of 4,500 feet.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 23 minutes,The objects were estimated to travel at speeds between 300-400 mph,Additional investigations may be warranted as the sighting remains classified as unidentified,The report was submitted by G. Yes Pittman,The event was part of the United States Air Force's Project Blue Book.
witness description: G. Yes Pittman, who observed the sighting.
